Officers are continuing to search for other suspects.
Supt Mark Payne said it was a "fast-paced investigation".
He added: "We are working closely with the school and if anyone has any information then I am urging them to speak to police or to call us as a matter of urgency."
City of Birmingham School is the main pupil referral unit for Birmingham, taking in children with a range of behavioural issues.
It has 10 sites across the city, and the stabbing occurred at its school in Fentham Road.
